items.title: 088/365: Planting season
items.description:
Kelvin P. Coleman posted a photo:

The soil in our garden has always been hell to work with, a sort of heavy clay, but this year Dad fancies trying to grow some vegetables. It’s something that we’ve done successfully in the past, so I see no reason why it shouldn’t work again this year. What strikes me as odd is that you have to plant potatoes in order to grow potatoes – the thing that you put in the ground at the start isn’t usually already the thing that it’s going to be when you dig it up at the end... is it?

29th March 2011 — GBR, Nottinghamshire

Canon PowerShot S5 IS
items.author: nobody@flickr.com (Kelvin P. Coleman)
